On May 28, 2009, Vice President Biden hosted two conference calls with Governors and Mayors/County Executives to discuss the implementation of the Recovery Act. The calls included discussions on the progress of the Recovery Act and updates on various projects. A total of 46 Governors and 66 Mayors/County Executives participated in the conference calls. This was part of ongoing efforts by the Vice President to engage with local officials and ensure the effective implementation of the Recovery Act.